Frequently needed Docker commands:

Start the services:
docker compose docker-compose.yml up -d

Dolibarr ERP:
http://localhost:8080

To STOP all containers run the below command:
sudo docker stop $(sudo docker ps -q)

# Remove containers + attached volumes to it.
docker compose down -v

To START all containers, run the below command:
docker start $(docker ps -a -q)

To DELETE all docker images, run the below command
sudo docker system prune --all --force --volumes

# Force remove all volumes
docker volume rm $(docker volume ls -q)

To execute an interactive shell inside a running Docker container, run the below command:
sudo docker exec -it <NAME> /bin/bash

Check all volumes:
docker volume ls

Delete volumes:
docker volume rm erpnext_docker_db-data erpnext_docker_sites erpnext_docker_logs erpnext_docker_redis-cache-data erpnext_docker_redis-queue-data

Delete all volume at once:
docker volume prune -f

remove leftover networks:
docker network prune -f

# See the service specific logs
docker compose logs scheduler --tail 200
docker compose logs queue-long --tail 200
docker compose logs backend --tail 200

# Copy data from docker to host machine:
docker cp sharmaa1-backend-1:/home/frappe/frappe-bench/apps/ganeshdistapp ./apps/

Restore backup on Dolibarr db:
To STOP all containers run the below command:
sudo docker stop $(sudo docker ps -q)

